# abt
Austere Backup Tool


Description
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Simple yet effective data archiving tool for UNIX/Linux servers



Features
---------------------------------------------------------------------
- Portable across POSIX systems and standardized UNIX Shell
- Automatic arive filename generation
- Preview (simulation) mode for testing



Installation
---------------------------------------------------------------------
git clone https://github.com/varnet/abt



Usage
---------------------------------------------------------------------
abt: Usage: [-n] 19 [-x|-X] file [-o] dir dir dir...
        -h            Show help
        -a, --alias          Specify archive alias (default: hostname)
        -D, --dstdir         Destination directory '/path/to/dir'
        -n, --renice         Change the process priority
        -o, --omitpath       Omit directory full path
        -p, --preview        Preview resulting archiver command
        -X, --exclude-from   Read exclusion from file
        -x, --exclude        Exclude file or directory




Reporting Bugs
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Use GitHub bug tracking system: 
https://github.com/varnet/abf/issues
